An Autopurger periodically removes noncondensibles from the system.  The fire control box outside the Machine Room is operated by fire department personnel in the event of emergency.  The Ammonia Diffusion Tank is maintained full of water to absorb a system overpressure release from the vessel pressure relief valves.  Emergency E-stop switches are located outside each Machine Room entrance for emergency shutdown.  Ammonia sensors in the Machine Room and cooling/freezing rooms trigger audible/visual notifications, liquid flow shutdown, purge ventilation activation, and equipment shutdown at prescribed levels.



The operation staff consists of the Maintenance Supervisor and two Refrigeration Operator/Mechanics .  Staff is responsible for the operation and the majority of the maintenance of the refrigeration system, as well as the daily monitoring.  Major maintenance activities are contracted to a qualified refrigeration contractor.  





Safety systems include:



1.    Pressure relief valves on all pressure vessels;

2.    Ammonia diffusion tank (all relief valve discharge lines lead to the diffusion tank for mixing with water in the event of a release from a component relief valve);

3.    Compressor safety cutouts and control panels to shut down the compressor operation if safe operating conditions are exceeded;

4.    Liquid level float switches and level columns;

5.    High level vessel alarms;

6.    Ventilation system for continuous and emergency ventilation;

